    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for the Morrison COU1 CFD hemolysis model at Model Risk Level 5 is accepted on the following grounds: (1) All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been fully assessed; 11 factors achieve exactly the required Gradation 4 level and 2 factors (Discretization Error, Relevance of QoI) exceed requirements at Gradation 5. No factor falls below its required level. (2) The primary acceptance criterion (RH < 1.0 relative hemolysis index vs. predicate device) is satisfied across all 5 operating points with E_n values 0.61–0.87, confirming adequate predictive accuracy within quantified uncertainty bounds. (3) Sensitivity analysis (LHS n=512, Sobol' decomposition) identifies tip clearance and rotational speed as dominant variance contributors; their uncertainties are bounded within the operating envelope and do not challenge the accept/reject decision. (4) Independent replication by a second analyst confirmed results within 0.8%, and the peer-reviewed boundary condition correction was minor (< 0.5% impact on NIH). (5) The full provenance chain from foundational PIV benchmark data through hemolysis bench measurements to the tolerance-sensitivity decision is documented and traceable. (6) No residual gaps in the evidence base were identified that would require offset rationale; all required credibility levels are met or exceeded. The model is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device within the documented operating envelope.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
